{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_54","type":"agent_message","text":"The first patch moved the failure forward. Log4j now gets past the missing method and resource lookup, but it hits a second native-image restriction: `ServiceLoaderUtil` builds a lambda class at runtime through `LambdaMetafactory`, and the image rejects that generated class unless it is captured as a predefined class. I’m checking how this repository stores predefined-class metadata so I can add the minimal remaining piece instead of guessing."}}
